#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.106"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.106:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.106:0.2"
msgid "11. Phāsuvihāravagga "
msgstr "11. Living Comfortably "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.106:0.3"
msgid "106. Ānandasutta "
msgstr "106. With Ānanda "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.106:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.106:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

# NOTE: BB and Com don’t remark on “sangha” here, but presumably it means, “while living in a community”, as opposed to living in seclusion. It doesn’t mean “while remaining as a mendicant”.
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.133, sc2
#. VAR: bhikkhu saṃghe → bhikkhusaṅgho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.106:2.1"
msgid "“Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how could a mendicant live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?” "

# NOTE: Sampavatta is unusual, “motivate” is more literal than BB’s “exhort”, which follows the Comm.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: attanā → attanā ca (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: no → no ca (mr)
#. VAR: sampavattā → sampavattā hoti (mr)
msgctxt "an5.106:2.2"
msgid "“Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle sampavattā; "
msgstr "“It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but they don’t motivate others to be ethical. "

msgctxt "an5.106:2.3"
msgid "ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a monastic community.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.106:3.1"
msgid "“Siyā pana, bhante, aññopi pariyāyo yathā bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, could there be another way for a mendicant to live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: ānanda → ānandāti bhagavā avoca (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.106:3.2"
msgid "“Siyā, ānanda. "
msgstr "“There could, Ānanda. "

